            "description": "Append a full memory breakdown table to the output (each contributing buffer + the calculation that produces server_buffers, per_thread_buffers, max_used_memory and max_peak_memory). Useful when a WARNING/CRITICAL fires and you need to see which buffer dominates the footprint.",
